import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.hist(data['age'], bins='auto', edgecolor='black')
    plt.xlabel('Age')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the age distribution of the victims?')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    gender_counts = data['gender'].value_counts()
    gender_counts.plot(kind='bar')
    plt.xlabel('Gender')
    plt.ylabel('Count')
    plt.title('What is the gender distribution of the victims?')
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    race_counts = data['race'].value_counts()
    plt.pie(race_counts, labels=race_counts.index, autopct='%1.1f%%')
    plt.title("What is the racial distribution of the victims?", wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
